# Test Analysis: heap_sort__opaque

## Source File
`core/source/sort/heap_sort__opaque.c`

## Spec File
`docs/specs/core/sort/heap_sort__opaque.h.spec.md`

## Test Report File
`scripts/test_report_digest/test_suite_sort_heap_sort__opaque.c.report`

## Summary

All 8 reported test failures are caused by a single root defect: the
`size_of__type` and `length_of__array` (element count) parameters are
swapped in the function signature relative to the specification.

## Defect

### DEF-001: Parameter order mismatch — `size_of__type` and `size_of__array` are swapped

**Severity:** Critical  
**Affects:** All tests

